{{zh-forms|[[抛]][[砖]][[引]][[玉]]|[[拋磚引玉]]}}
==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
[[Pinyin]]: pāo zhuān yĭn yù
===Etymology===
Literally: to throw a brick and to get a piece of jade in return
===Idiom===
# a self-depracating way to express the idea of offering one's own relatively worthless words, opinions or services in order to solicit the more valued words, opinions or services of others
#: ''20[[多]][[年]][[前]]，[[曾]][[琦]][[是]][[第]][[一]][[个]][[到]][[厦门]][[投资]][[的]][[港商]]，[[当时]][[他]][[想]][[的]][[就是]][[当]][[一]][[个]]“'''抛砖引玉'''[[的]][[人]]”，[[让]][[更]][[多]][[的]][[港]]、[[澳]]、[[台]]、[[侨]][[商]][[回国]][[投资]]。[http://64.233.167.104/search?q=cache:0rJpgUXfd7YJ:www.cbt.com.cn/cbtnews/frontend/news.asp%3FID%3D96094+%22%E6%8A%9B%E7%A0%96%E5%BC%95%E7%8E%89%22+site:.cn&hl=zh-CN&gl=cn&ct=clnk&cd=19]''
#: ''More than 20 years ago, Zeng Qi was the first Hong Kong businessman to go to [[Xiamen]] to invest.  At the time, he thought of himself as a '''a plain rock that attracts jade''', making it possible for even more businessmen from [[Hong Kong]], [[Macao]] and [[Taiwan]] to return to the Motherland to invest''.

